    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I am not a current member of the core team, but I used to be a couple of summers ago. I can confirm what @iFA88 says. That's one of the reasons (there are others) that OpenEthereum requires a 12 TB hard drive and Erigon requires a 2TB hard drive. You can't have everything.\r\n\r\nI switched officially from OpenEthereum to Erigon about a year and half ago. The main reason why I didn't do so earlier was because of the exact issue you describe. One of the things that we found to be very beneficial was to use `trace_block`. In fact, in our testing, Erigon's `trace_block` was faster than OpenEthereum's `trace_block`. I can't explain why this was the case, but it may have been another engineering choice -- perhaps Erigon optimizes `trace_block` whereas OpenEthereum chose to optimize `trace_transaction`.\r\n\r\nFor our application, the speed of `trace_block` is excellent, and I would argue that very small disc space usage is very much worth any performance differences.\r\n\r\nHaving said all of this. I am no longer a core dev on Erigon, so not exactly what you asked for.",
