    "body": "My guess is that it will be a very long time before such a flag appears. (Not speaking for the team, of course).\r\n\r\nI actually don't think you're correct when you say that \"for indexing the chain, those performance numbers are not feasible.\" 30-second return time is, but we're not seeing that at all.\r\n\r\nWe have a locally running version of Erigon and our software (TrueBlocks) indexes the entire chain on **a laptop computer** (admittedly a pretty massive one - 64GB of Ram, 8TB hard drive) in under two days. And this is an astronomically deep index. We visit every block, every transaction, every log, every receipt, and every trace and find many billions of address appearances (that is, `<block_number>.<tx_id>` pairs per address).\r\n\r\nI'm very sure there's something wrong with your setup. My guess is an under-provisioned machine.\r\n\r\nHope this is helpful. I'd be very interested to learn what you find. And, please remember, I'm not speaking for the team.\r\n",
